OL,3,C'No routes' for storm compensation
OL,5,F"If NIE Networks was to voluntarily
OL,6,Fdecline to apply the severe weather
OL,7,Fexemption, customers would pay 50% of
OL,8,Fthe cost of compensation through their
OL,9,Felectricity bills next year and NIE
OL,10,Fshareholders would have to agree to
OL,11,Fbear the rest.
OL,13,F"No other electricity company
OL,14,Fshareholders in Britain or Ireland
OL,15,Fhave been asked to bear the cost of
OL,16,Fcompensation for Storm Eowyn, which
OL,17,Fwas an unprecedented weather event and
OL,18,FNIE was not at fault for the
OL,19,Fdisruption caused by the storm."
